# Build context exclusions for the Dockerfiles under Docker/.
#
# Every Dockerfile does `COPY . .` from the repository root, so anything not
# excluded here is uploaded as build context and baked into the builder layer.
# target/ alone is multiple gigabytes and is rebuilt inside the image anyway,
# and any change to an excluded artefact would otherwise invalidate cached
# layers.

# Build output
target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock
**/Cargo.lock

# Version control
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# The Dockerfiles themselves are never needed inside the image
Docker/

# Local run / secret material must never enter the build context
.run/
.env
.secrets
.local/

# Coverage and profiling output
coverage/
cobertura.xml
tarpaulin-report.*
*.profraw
*.profdata
*.zip

# Editor and OS noise
.idea/
.vscode/
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
**/*.rs.bk

# Documentation that no build step reads
doc/
*.md
!README.md
